Double Entry Accounting

Every transaction has at least 2 sides – debit and credit.
Debits always equal credits.
Accounts increase/decrease depending on their type:

One account is debited (Dr)
One account is credited (Cr)
The total debits must always equal total credits. This ensures the accounting equation stays balanced:

Assets=Liabilities+Equity

Asset        ↑ Debit  | ↓ Credit
Liability    ↑ Credit | ↓ Debit
Equity       ↑ Credit | ↓ Debit
Revenue      ↑ Credit | ↓ Debit
Expense      ↑ Debit  | ↓ Credit

